              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 11,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "36e474dd2f4c19b317214eccf55c8c77",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Medium",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 5 feet, *Reach (Long):* 5 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 160,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "20f6f5f93a453f3006eb194c6d712042",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Undead",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Once living, these creatures were infused after death with void energy and soul-corrupting unholy magic. When reduced to 0 Hit Points, an undead creature is destroyed. Undead creatures are damaged by vitality energy and are healed by void energy, and don\u2019t benefit from healing vitality effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "defense": {
      "ac": {
        "subtype": "armor_class",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "value": 26
      },
      "automatic_abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "name": "Root Spawn",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "A living creature slain by a rootridden that had a lower level than the rootridden rises as a new rootridden after 1d10 rounds, on its turn. This new rootridden is under the command of the rootridden that created it. If the creator is destroyed, any rootridden it created in the past 24 hours are destroyed as well, immediately collapsing into inert plant matter.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 134,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Primal",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 460,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "links": [
                {
                  "alt": "holy",
                  "aonid": 517,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "name": "holy",
                  "type": "link"
                }
              ],
              "name": "Unholy",
              "sources": [
                {
